    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1876-04-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1876-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="335" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                <head>No. 326.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Comanos</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Agency
                                        and Consulate-General of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Cairo, Egypt</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1876-04-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 21, 1876</date>. (Received May 11.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 22.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to announce the
                            unexpected return of H. H. Hassan Pasha, third son of the Khedive, from
                            the Abyssinian expedition on the 13th instant.</p>
                <p>It is rumored that the Egyptian forces have been defeated with great <pb facs="0659" n="603" xml:id="pg_603"/> loss. Prince Hassan complains
                            of the cowardice of the Egyptian troops, many of whom threw down their
                            arms and fled when attacked by the Abyssinians.</p>
                <p>His Highness the Khedive has called out the Bashi Bazouks and Bedouin,
                            irregular troops, and dispatched them to the seat of war.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>N. D. COMANOS,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Vice-Consul-General, in
                                    charge</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
